               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#ai-catalogue">
                     <p>الفصول المهمة في معرفة الأئمة</p>
                     <p>Another work on the Twelve Imáms, entitled Al-Fuşúlu'l-muhimma fi ma'rifati- <lb/>
                l-A'imma, defective at the beginning and consequently lacking the author's name <lb/>
                which, however, as we learn from Brockelmann (11, 176) is Núru'd-Din 'Ali <lb/>
                ibn Muhammad ibnu's-Sabbágh (d. 855/1451). For description of contents see <lb/>
                Ahlwardt's Berlin Arabic Catalogue, vol. IX, pp. 212-213, Nos. 9671-2.</p>
                     <p>Ff. 202 of 18.5 x 12 c. and 18 ll.; good naskh with rubrications, dated 9 Rabí 1, <lb/>
                1178/Sept. 14, 1861; scribe, 'Abdu'l-Aziz ibn Sa'id [ibn] al-Hajj Ahmad an-Najjár. <lb/>
                Bought on Nov. 12, 1920, from the Belshah collection.</p>
                  </summary>
